post_text: We are launching our Learning Management System (LMS) to all students and parents across the district. It is called Schoology and it is a one-stop-shop for all student activities, teacher feedback, and parent communication. It is also a great place for collaboration with teachers, parents, and students. This coming week (Monday and Tuesday), we will be offering synchronous Parent Tech Boot Camps to cover Schoology. If you are not able to make the training, we will be sending our tutorial videos as well. Please fill out the form to let us know about your interest in attending one of the sessions. We are hoping to keep them small so it is easier to field questions and have that one on one experience. We will send you a Zoom link when you indicate which session you would like to attend. We are looking forward to working with you! Here is the interest form: https://forms.gle/frdANd14W6mKiEwKA

Please see the following letter from Dr. Andy Johnsen, LUSD Superintendent, regarding the district's reopening plan. Attached is also the outline of the distance learning model.

Dr. Johnsen states in the letter that, "We are currently working with our teachers to finalize plans for our distance learning model and will communicate that to all families shortly. It will include daily teacher interaction, a social-emotional learning
component, and also incorporate many of the lessons learned from the spring to increase the academic rigor and engagement of our students."

Ready, set, distance learn! Monday, April 20th, will be a whole new world for students and teachers! Our staff has developed standards based, engaging activities for each grade level. Teachers will be connecting to students via virtual classrooms! We are so excited to be together again..in the virtual world! Paper packets will be distributed at school sites (except Eucalyptus Hills) for those who require them, between 9:00am and 11:00am on Monday morning. (Eucalyptus Hills packets will be distributed at the LUSD District office). Please visit our new Distance Learning website!

https://tinyurl.com/lusddistancelearning

post_text: This week is the International Hour of Code! According to Dr. Mitch Resnick, MIT professor, "when we learn to code, we are learning how to organize, express, and share ideas in new ways, in a new medium." Coding also challenges our students to create and problem-solve repeatedly, which makes them persevere relentlessly. Please join with LUSD in supporting unplugged and plugged in coding this week! Visit the Hour of Code resource site for more information! https://bit.ly/2P3fcNv

post_text: This week, 4th grade students at Riverview International experienced the Butterfly Project! The Butterfly Project is a call to action through education, the arts and memorial making. It uses the lessons of the Holocaust to educate about the dangers of hatred and bigotry and cultivates empathy and social responsibility. The culminating project is a painted ceramic butterfly that represents a child in the Holocaust. The message sent is that this will NEVER AGAIN happen. Thank you to our retired Riverview teacher and Butterfly Project presenter, Arlene Keeyes, for bringing the program to our district! #LUSDlearns #RiverviewInternational #NeverAgain #ButterflyProject

post_text:
Attention LUSD parents: Have you registered for the Parent Portal? Beginning in the 2019-2020 school year, the Parent Portal will give you one-stop easy access to your child’s information, such as attendance, grades, report cards, and assessments. You can even email your child’s teacher through the portal, and register new students to the district.

The directions to create your Parent Portal account were mailed home in November. If you have misplaced the information with the access code, please call your child’s school, and they can help. Please register as soon as possible!

If you have a child who is completely new to the Lakeside District, the online registration begins on March 1st.

post_text:
A big welcome to Mr. Jim Rosa, the new principal at Lakeside Farms School. Mr. Rosa has lived in the community of Lakeside for over ten years and is blessed with three children: a boy in 2nd grade, a daughter beginning Kindergarten, and a boy in Preschool. His wife is a 2nd grade teacher.

Mr. Rosa began his career as an intermediate teacher in Santee at a K-6 school and moved into administration from there where he has worked as a Vice Principal at two K-8 schools. Mr. Rosa loves to spend time outdoors and with his family. He especially loves camping and golf. Becoming a principal in Lakeside is a dream come true. He has gotten to know many wonderful people from his time at Lakeside National Little League and looks forward to getting to know many other Lakeside families. #lusdlearns

Did you know? LUSD has been invited to sit on a panel at the statewide Community of Practice-Science in Sacramento next week. LUSD will be represented by Zulma Santana and David Tupper; David will endeavor to tell the district's "story" i.e. leveraging science to build language, policies/procedures that help support that, and next steps....Zulma will relay how it actually works in a classroom with real kids, what supports are needed, and our learnings so far...
They will also show a video that Priscilla Barcellos made that highlights how science can help create space and context for language and literacy development even for the little ones.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3KYfrtr_CgI&feature=youtu.be

post_text:
Congratulations to Tessa Green who was confirmed Monday night by the LUSD Board of Trustees for the position of Vice Principal at Tierra del Sol Middle. Although many applied for the position, Tessa was the unanimous choice of the interview team and has the full support of the board.

Since December of 2013, she has been the Lead Teacher at Eucalyptus Hills and successfully supported the TK and EAK programs with Mr. Brown. She came to us from Clark County School District in Las Vegas with 14 years of teaching experience across all grade levels, including two years teaching high needs, emotionally-disturbed students. She earned her Administrative Credential from National University. Ms. Green is excited to join the excellent team at TdS. Along with her love of education, she also is the mother of two wonderful kids, 12 year-old son, Dominic, and 5 year-old daughter Isabella. Please help us welcome Tessa to the TdS family!
